<item>
            <title>[HBASE-15383] Load distribute across secondary read replicas for meta</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15383</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, we always hit the primary replica for meta and fallback to the secondary replicas in case of a timeout. This can hamper performance in scenarios where meta becomes a hot region e.g. cluster ramp up..clients dropping connections etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s good to have a load distribution approach on meta&apos;s secondary replicas with fallback to primary if we read stale data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
